    Suppose that <fr:tex>S</fr:tex> is connected, and let <fr:tex>\mathcal {C}</fr:tex> be a strictly full subcategory of the category of continuous families of Hodge <fr:tex>\mathbb {Q}</fr:tex>-structures on <fr:tex>S</fr:tex>.
    We will have need of the following conditions:

    <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1497</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Condition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2.1.xml</fr:route><fr:number>4.2.2.1</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p><fr:tex>\mathcal {C}</fr:tex> is stable under direct factors, direct sums, and tensor products;
        the Tate constant families <fr:tex>\mathbb {Q} (n)</fr:tex> (for <fr:tex>n \in \mathbb {Z}</fr:tex>) are in <fr:tex>\mathcal {C}</fr:tex>.
      </fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

    <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1498</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Condition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2.2.xml</fr:route><fr:number>4.2.2.2</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
        Every homogeneous (of some weight <fr:tex>n</fr:tex>) Hodge structure in <fr:tex>\mathcal {C}</fr:tex> is polarisable.
      </fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

    <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1499</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Condition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2.3</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2.3.xml</fr:route><fr:number>4.2.2.3</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
        For every <fr:tex>H \in \operatorname {Ob} \mathcal {C}</fr:tex>, there exists a local system <fr:tex>H'_ \mathbb {Z}</fr:tex> on <fr:tex>S</fr:tex> of free <fr:tex>\mathbb {Z}</fr:tex>-modules such that <fr:tex>H'_ \mathbb {Z} \otimes \mathbb {Q} \approx  H_ \mathbb {Q}</fr:tex>.
      </fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

